  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Examining Static Data**\n\nI\'m currently focused on creating a `/src/data.ts` file to hold initial state data for the applet. My goal is to make it easy to load static images and placeholders directly from the HTML, specifically using those hotlinked from the HTML. I\'m taking a look at those links to begin. The first is for Leader Pastor Alex Rivera.\n\n\n**Identifying Image Sources**\n\nI\'ve got three distinct image URLs for Alex Rivera\'s avatar now: long, obscure Googleusercontent links. I\'m taking the longest one of the three to use as the base for now. I\'m focusing on the formatting of the `data.ts` and the associated import statements now, aiming for brevity and readability.\n\n\n**Analyzing Image Details**\n\nI\'ve discovered all the images are high-fidelity, which is great for the applet. I am now examining three more image sources: a scanner background, the Next Gen Leadership Summit cover, and avatars for Youth Members. I\'ll need to figure out the best way to handle these varying image sources.\n\n\n**Adding More Data**\n\nI\'ve just added three more image URLs to the data: those for Kenji Sato, Liam Smith, and Zahara Williams. They\'re all long Googleusercontent links again. I\'ll need to figure out how to format these with the existing data.\n\n\n**Incorporating More Images**\n\nI\'ve just added three more images. There is a portrait for an Admin Leader from the Central Hub, and another for Head Leader Marcus Chen. I\'ve also included a profile image for the Attendance Live Scanner. I\'m formatting these now.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/data.ts` to pre-populate the application with high-fidelity, interactive mock data matching the exact figures and images from the EMBER screenshots. This includes members, events, moderation queue items, and prayer board cards."
