    thinking: "**Constructing The Core**\n\nI\'ve successfully finalized the modular components. Currently, I have `types.ts` for type structures, `data.ts` with mock data, a responsive `Sidebar.tsx`, the `DashboardOverview.tsx` for metrics and actions, and a `MembersDirectory.tsx` for youth records with their functionalities. Next, I will begin linking these modular components together and developing the application logic.\n\n\n**Expanding Application Scope**\n\nI\'ve scoped out several new components: `AnnouncementsHub`, `EventsManager`, `ModerationHub`, and `AttendanceScannerView`, each with specific functionalities. These components are designed to be extremely modular, keeping files concise and within token limits. I\'m now turning my attention to `src/App.tsx`, verifying its current state before implementing reactive state management for `activeTab`, `members`, `announcements`, `events`, `submissions`, and `prayerItems`.\n\n\n**Defining State Handlers**\n\nI\'m now implementing event handlers to manage application state. Specifically, `onAddMember` will generate unique ember IDs and include joined dates. `onUpdateMember` will update existing member data. I\'m also working on `onAddAnnouncement`, which adds new announcements, and `onAddEvent` to create and format new event details. Lastly, I\'m defining functions for submission management.\n\n\n"
