  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Summarizing Build Success**\n\nI\'m thrilled with the flawless build completion! I\'ve successfully implemented all user requests, adhering meticulously to guidelines. Now, I\'m focusing on crafting a concise, design-forward summary that aligns perfectly with our specified communication style. This polished summary will highlight the project\'s key accomplishments.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the responsive website implementation for the **EMBER Youth Leader Portal**, designing it for mobile, tablet, and desktop viewports. The design utilizes a dark-tech aesthetic utilizing deep charcoal grays, custom high-contrast orange accent headers, and glass cards with generous negative space. \n\nHere is a summary of the custom views and responsive features implemented:\n\n### 1. Responsive Shell Layout\n- **Dynamic Navigation Sidebar**: Stays fixed to the left on desktop viewports and transitions into a slide-out overlay drawer on mobile and tablet screens.\n- **Unified Header**: Features responsive breadcrumbs, a live clock synchronized to the system time, and real-time counter alerts showing active pending items.\n\n### 2. Live Overview Dashboard\n- **Analytics Scoreboard**: Displays key metrics including total youth, urgent registrations, active prayer requests, and attendance percentages with present vs. absent splits.\n- **Recent Registration & Activity Log**: Features an in-container search bar and a \"Load More\" action which dynamically appends interactive user logs.\n- **Action Queue & Mini Calendar**: Prioritizes key leadership alerts with actionable reminders, fast routing triggers, and card listings for immediate events.\n\n### 3. Interactive Youth Directory\n- **Bento Data Table**: Organizes member profiles with high-resolution avatars, custom level badges (**Ignition**, **Blaze**, **Inferno**), and toggles for active status.\n- **Search & Filters**: Allows live search query lookups and dropdown filters for sorting members alphabetically or filtering by active levels.\n- **Modals & Exports**: Supports adding new members with optional photo uploads and exporting the filtered directory instantly.\n\n### 4. Announcements Bulletin & Phone Mockup\n- **Dynamic Split View**: Features the active/draft announcement listings on the left, paired with an input creation form on the right.\n- **Live Mobile Mockup Preview**: Implements an interactive smartphone preview on the page. As leaders type custom descriptions, adjust priority tiers, or swap cover templates, the simulated smartphone screen renders the updates in real time.\n\n### 5. Events Calendar & Scheduler\n- **Monthly Grid**: Displays a calendar grid complete with calendar cards (e.g., *Youth Night Live*, *Ember Summit*).\n- **Roster Controls**: Integrates registration progress trackers, broadcast buttons, and options to update capacity levels or trigger test check-ins.\n- **Interactive Event Creator**: Allows leaders to register custom events that instantly render inside the appropriate monthly calendar cells and upcoming schedules.\n\n### 6. Workflow Center & Prayer Kanban\n- **Moderation Stack**: Hosts pending testimonies and devotional submissions. Approving a student\'s testimony moves it out of the queue and automatically publishes it.\n- **Prayer Kanban Board**: Implements columns (**New Queue**, **Active Prayer**, and **Archived**) to manage prayer cards. Navigational chevrons shift requests between columns, automatically tracking and displaying active prayer counts.\n- **System Footers**: Displays live diagnostic specs showing active data nodes and latency states.\n\n### 7. Attendance Scanner view\n- **Simulated Camera Viewfinder**: Features a background POV photo of the church hall overlaid with scanning brackets and green laser line loops.\n- **QR Simulation Match**: Clicking the mock QR trigger completes a simulated check-in, rendering soundwave pulses and showing student readouts with confirmation timestamps."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 7447456
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
